snippet: Kamala Harris stood out from the 10-person crowd several times during the NBC debate. Her exchange with Joe Biden, who is leading in the polls, put him on the defensive.

snippet: Even 16 months before Election Day, interest in the campaign is intense. Wednesday’s TV audience nearly equaled the record for a Democratic primary debate.
lead_paragraph: MIAMI — Nearly 15.3 million Americans tuned in on Wednesday for the first debate of the Democratic nominating contest for president, a higher number than NBC News producers had anticipated and a sign of significant national interest in the 2020 campaign.
abstract: Even 16 months before Election Day, interest in the campaign is intense. Wednesday’s TV audience nearly equaled the record for a Democratic primary debate.

snippet: A big health care experiment for Democrats shows how fiercely doctors and hospitals will fight.
lead_paragraph: For those who dream of universal health care, Washington State looks like a pioneer. As Gov. Jay Inslee pointed out in the first Democratic presidential debate on Wednesday, his state has created the country’s first “public option” — a government-run health plan that would compete with private insurance.
abstract: A big health care experiment for Democrats shows how fiercely doctors and hospitals will fight.

headline_main: Democratic Debate, Border Aid, Boeing: Your Thursday Briefing

snippet: Detailed plans can tell a candidate’s story about what kind of person she is — and what kind of president she would be.
lead_paragraph: There are plenty of good arguments against running a presidential campaign the way Senator Elizabeth Warren is doing it, with a heavy emphasis on detailed policy proposals.
